The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence at the installation ceremony of General Mark A. Milley as the 20th Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff. Pence expressed gratitude to General Joseph F. Dunford for his service and congratulated General Milley on his new role. He praised President Trump for his commitment to strengthening the military and highlighted accomplishments such as securing the largest investment in national defense in a generation, initiating the modernization of the nuclear arsenal, and establishing the United States Space Force. Pence emphasized that Trump's top priority is the safety and security of the nation. The article concludes with Pence introducing President Trump at the ceremony.